sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Registry as model-registry REST<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 1: Model Registry REST API Access (with kube-rbac-proxy)

    Client->>Router: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Router->>Proxy: HTTPS/8443<br/>TLS reencrypt
    Proxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/6443<br/>Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>Proxy: Authorized
    Proxy->>Registry: HTTP/8080<br/>plaintext (localhost)
    Registry->>DB: 5432/TCP or 3306/TCP<br/>configurable SSL<br/>Password Auth
    DB-->>Registry: Query Results
    Registry-->>Proxy: REST Response
    Proxy-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>Client: HTTPS Response

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 2: Operator Reconciliation

    participant Operator as Model Registry Operator

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch ModelRegistry CRs<br/>HTTPS/6443<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: ModelRegistry CR Event
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Deployment,<br/>Service, Route, RBAC,<br/>NetworkPolicy<br/>HTTPS/6443
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Resource Created/Updated
    Operator->>K8sAPI: OpenShift API Discovery<br/>(platform detection)<br/>HTTPS/6443
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: API Capabilities

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 3: Model Catalog Data Loading

    participant InitData as catalog-data-init<br/>(init container)
    participant InitBench as benchmark-data-init<br/>(init container)
    participant Catalog as model-catalog<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant CatDB as catalog-postgres<br/>5432/TCP

    InitData->>InitData: Load models-catalog.yaml,<br/>validated-models-catalog.yaml,<br/>other-models-catalog.yaml<br/>to emptyDir volume
    InitBench->>InitBench: Load benchmark metrics<br/>to emptyDir volume
    Catalog->>Catalog: Read ConfigMap volumes<br/>(catalog sources)
    Catalog->>CatDB: PostgreSQL/5432<br/>plaintext<br/>Password (Secret)
    CatDB-->>Catalog: Persisted catalog data
